<subSubSection id="B1D817C8FF9DFFDC8FA2FEFA780967B5" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F97D4443FF9DFFDC8FA2FEFA780967B5" blockId="22.[151,1437,298,847]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="CBB69851FF9DFFDC8FA2FEFA7C1D64E5" bold="true" box="[197,325,373,399]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="3EC23FC0FF9DFFDC8E2BFEFA7F7364E4" box="[332,555,373,398]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcatus">
<emphasis id="CBB69851FF9DFFDC8E2BFEFA7F7364E4" box="[332,555,373,398]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Epeorus bifurcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a smaller species (length to 
<quantity id="3E3AE9A6FF9DFFDC8CF1FEFA7EB564E5" box="[918,1005,373,399]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
), recognizable by a pair of relatively short submedian spines on terga I–IX, flatly elliptical head (
<bibRefCitation id="9D5339B2FF9DFFDC8C32FE15793964DE" author="Nguyen" box="[853,1121,410,436]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Nguyen, V. V. &amp; Bae, Y. J. (2004 a) Larvae of the Heptageniid Mayfly Genus Epeorus (Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae) from Vietnam. Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology, 7, 19 - 28." type="book chapter" year="2004" yearSuffix="a">
Nguyen &amp; Bae, 
<number id="4F0A5664FF9DFFDC8B72FE15790C64DE" box="[1045,1108,410,436]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="2004.0">2004</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
: p. 
<number id="4F0A5664FF9DFFDC8BEEFE1579F164DE" box="[1161,1193,410,436]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="21.0">21</number>
, Figs. 7,9), posterior margins of terga with densely rowed blunt bristles, surface of terga with very fine scattered setae, only a weak fringe of small setae shorter than spines in the medial groove of terga and with triangular gill I of same length as following gills, all equally ovaloid, and femora with spot (
<bibRefCitation id="9D5339B2FF9DFFDC8C1FFD8578D7674E" author="Braasch" box="[888,1423,522,548]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Braasch, D. &amp; Soldan, T. (1979) Neue Heptageniidae aus Asien (Ephemeroptera). Reichenbachia, 17 (31), 261 - 272." type="journal article" year="1979" yearSuffix="p">
Braasch &amp; Soldán 
<number id="4F0A5664FF9DFFDC8B3AFD8579C5674E" box="[1117,1181,522,548]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1979.0">1979</number>
: p. 
<number id="4F0A5664FF9DFFDC8BD9FD8579A8674E" box="[1214,1264,522,548]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="266.0">266</number>
, Figs. 
<number id="4F0A5664FF9DFFDC8A27FD8578D7674E" box="[1344,1423,522,548]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="18.5" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="15.0">15–22</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Contrastingly, 
<emphasis id="CBB69851FF9DFFDC8E24FDBF7C806723" box="[323,472,560,585]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="3EC23FC0FF9DFFDC8E24FDBF7C8C6723" box="[323,468,560,585]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhithralis">E. rhithralis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
as well as 
<taxonomicName id="3EC23FC0FF9DFFDC8D31FDBF7FB46723" box="[598,748,560,585]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcatus">
<emphasis id="CBB69851FF9DFFDC8D31FDBF7FB46723" box="[598,748,560,585]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. bifurcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, have ovaloid shape of head, long elliptic form of first gill, pointed bristles on posterior margins of terga and lack of groove on terga (
<bibRefCitation id="9D5339B2FF9DFFDC8B6BFDDA79EC6705" author="Braasch" box="[1036,1204,597,623]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Braasch, D. (1980) Eintagsfliegen (Gattungen Epeorus und Iron) aus Nepal (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae). Reichenbachia, 18 (7), 56 - 65." type="journal article" year="1980">
Braasch 
<number id="4F0A5664FF9DFFDC8B12FDDA79EC6705" box="[1141,1204,597,623]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: p. 
<number id="4F0A5664FF9DFFDC8BB9FDDA79A66705" box="[1246,1278,597,623]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="63.0">63</number>
, Figs. 
<number id="4F0A5664FF9DFFDC8A29FDDA78056705" box="[1358,1373,597,623]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="4.0">4</number>
b–l). Other species from the region are either without any spines as 
<emphasis id="CBB69851FF9DFFDC8CE0FDF5782A67F9" box="[903,1394,634,659]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="3EC23FC0FF9DFFDC8CE0FDF579FE67F9" box="[903,1190,634,659]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hieroglyphicus">Epeorus hieroglyphicus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3EC23FC0FF9DFFDC8BD5FDF5782A67F9" box="[1202,1394,634,659]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khayengensis">E. khayengensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3EC23FC0FF9DFFDC8AE5FDF57C4967D3" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Iron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papillatus">
<emphasis id="CBB69851FF9DFFDC8AE5FDF57C4967D3" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. papillatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3EC23FC0FF9DFFDC8E45FD2F7C9B67D3" box="[290,451,672,697]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Iron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suspicatus">
<emphasis id="CBB69851FF9DFFDC8E45FD2F7C9B67D3" box="[290,451,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. suspicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3EC23FC0FF9DFFDC8EB3FD2F7ED467D0" authority="Braasch &amp; Soldan, 1984" authorityName="Braasch &amp; Soldan" authorityYear="1984" box="[468,908,672,698]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiberius">
<emphasis id="CBB69851FF9DFFDC8EB3FD2F7F0C67D3" box="[468,596,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. tiberius</emphasis>
Braasch &amp; Soldán, 
<number id="4F0A5664FF9DFFDC8C2BFD2F7ED467D0" box="[844,908,672,698]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</taxonomicName>
, or provided with pairs of tubercles like 
<taxonomicName id="3EC23FC0FF9DFFDC8AE5FD2F7C5D67B4" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhithralis">
<emphasis id="CBB69851FF9DFFDC8AE5FD2F7C5D67B4" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. rhithralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or with pairs of long spines like 
<taxonomicName id="3EC23FC0FF9DFFDC8DE0FD4A7E4F67B4" box="[647,791,709,734]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeatus">
<emphasis id="CBB69851FF9DFFDC8DE0FD4A7E4F67B4" box="[647,791,709,734]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. aculeatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3EC23FC0FF9DFFDC8C41FD4A792A67B5" authority="Braasch, 1980" authorityName="Braasch" authorityYear="1980" box="[806,1138,709,735]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis id="CBB69851FF9DFFDC8C41FD4A7E9B67B4" box="[806,963,709,734]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">E. bispinosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="9D5339B2FF9DFFDC8CADFD4A792A67B5" author="Braasch" box="[970,1138,709,735]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Braasch, D. (1980) Eintagsfliegen (Gattungen Epeorus und Iron) aus Nepal (Ephemeroptera, Heptageniidae). Reichenbachia, 18 (7), 56 - 65." type="journal article" year="1980">
Braasch, 
<number id="4F0A5664FF9DFFDC8B50FD4A792A67B5" box="[1079,1138,709,735]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3EC23FC0FF9DFFDC8BCDFD4A781267B4" box="[1194,1354,709,734]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Iron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martensi">
<emphasis id="CBB69851FF9DFFDC8BCDFD4A781267B4" box="[1194,1354,709,734]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Iron martensi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
